# Allowed IP Addresses and CIDR Ranges
#
# Format: One IP or CIDR range per line
# Lines starting with # are comments and will be ignored
# Empty lines are ignored
#
# Examples:
# 10.0.0.0/16          - Allows entire 10.0.x.x range (65,536 IPs)
# 192.168.1.0/24       - Allows 192.168.1.0 - 192.168.1.255 (256 IPs)
# 203.0.113.50/32      - Allows single IP address
#
# IMPORTANT: If this file doesn't exist or is empty, NO IP restrictions
# will be applied (current behavior - publicly accessible with auth)
#
# To enable IP restrictions:
# 1. Copy this file to: allowed-ips.txt
# 2. Add your VPN/office CIDR ranges below
# 3. Deploy: npx cdk deploy
#
# Example configuration:

# Main VPN range
# 10.0.0.0/16

# Backup VPN
# 10.1.0.0/16

# Office network
# 192.168.1.0/24

# Specific admin IP
# 203.0.113.50/32
